The paper analyzes the online response to preprints submitted to arXiv.org, which is a preprint database for computer science and other fields. The paper focuses on three forms of responses to these preprints: downloads on the arXiv.org site, mentions on Twitter, and early citations in the scholarly record. Given this focus, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which includes research on social media and online communities. Other likely sub-categories include cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.SD (Software Engineering), and cs.CY (Computers and Society), which all have relevance to the study of online information and communication.
